Guest (4)

Every night, the current owner of this card can send it to attach itself to another player's card, roleblocking it while its attached. That player will then own the card and can use it to vote during the day. If the card the Guest is currently attached to dies, Guest will also die. When the Guest leaves the original deck containing it, it will show it as (missing) and therefore cant be targeted. When this card dies, it will return to the original deck labeled dead. Alignment: (Villager) Aura: Good

Witch (10)

Witch has 6 potions. Healing potion can be used to protect a card at night, and is only consumed when it successfully saves from an attack. Killing potion can be used to kill a card at the end of the night, and is consumed even if it was blocked by protection. Fresh Potion can be used to win the game, while Spoiled Potion kills all of your cards. Protect Potion will protect all of your cards, but make them vulnerable to any attacks the next night. Engineer (12)

Starts with 200 metal and gains 30 metal every night. At night can build one of these structures:
  • Sentry costs 130 metal. Sentry is placed on one of your cards; cards attacking it will be killed by Sentry and their protection will be bypassed (but it won't protect the card from attacks). After 2 attacks it dies. Engineer can use 150 metal ONCE to repair it and activate it same night (but it won't change the target on which it is placed)
  • Dispenser costs 100 metal. Dispenser is placed between 2 neighbour cards, heals both of them so they won't die at night, dies after protecting from 2 attacks and cannot be repaired.
  • Teleporter costs 100 metal. Engineer can place an entrance and an exit on one of his attackers and on an opponent's card. Attacking that card afterwards will ignore protection, Teleporter doesn't count as a protection.
  • Everything, after placed, will turn on the next night.
  • Moving one of the structures at night costs 50 metal and Engineer cannot build new structures while moving one of them.
Alignment: Villager Aura: Unknown

Vanity (9)

Every night, select an enemy card and a target. You will copy that card's ability and use it on the target. You cannot receive feedback or information about the ability and the person vanity'd will receive the info and Vanity cannot select the same enemy card for the rest of the game. Abilities that does not have a specific target & Factional ww/solo kills cannot be copied. If a card doesn't have any charges of ability left, its ability cannot be copied too. Team: Miscellaneous Aura: Unknown

Ancestor (6)

At night, you can select two or more cards to make them a tribe. This selection can't be changed. The first time a card from the tribe is attacked, it will be saved (except for day lynch). The second time a card from the tribe is attacked, it will die, and the saved card will die too. You can then make a new tribe. Alignment: Villager Aura: Good Passive protection

Mr. Schrodinger (5)

This card owns 2 card slots. Each night, this card can choose which of the two card slots to occupy until the next night. Any interaction with the unoccupied slot will result to nothing, any information checks will say "No information was received". Alignment: Villager Aura: Good
6:18 PM

Fortune Teller's information:

Guest (4)

Every night, the current owner of this card can send it to attach itself to another player's card, roleblocking it while its attached. That player will then own the card and can use it to vote during the day. If the card the Guest is currently attached to dies, Guest will also die. When the Guest leaves the original deck containing it, it will show it as (missing) and therefore cant be targeted. When this card dies, it will return to the original deck labeled dead. Alignment: Villager Aura: Good

Stacker (6)

Each day he can choose to not vote to stack his current vote. Stacker can use stacked votes in day votings, but each stacked vote works only one time. Stacker can use up to 4 votes at once maximum. Alignment: Villager Aura: Good

Cat (5)

Once per game you may reveal the highest valued card of one of your opponents' deck and its location. On night 1 send a message that says: "Announcement from an Unknown Card: 9hi nub". Alignment: Villager Aura: Good

Caterpillar (5)

Each night can lay a seed on one of your cards. Next night, that card will form a cocoon around it, thus protecting it for the next 6 phases, after which it breaks. A card cannot perform its abilities while inside the cocoon. Already placed/existing abilities will still work. Cocoon breaks on the first attack or lynch attempt. Cocoon can also be broken manually, but manually breaking it takes one phase during which a card cannot be protected.

Diplomat (5)

You automatically win if more than half of the alive cards belong to you, and if Diplomat is still alive. Alignment: Miscellaneous Aura: Unknown

Herbalist [9]

At night can make a potion with 2 ingredients. Herbalist starts with 3 Herb, 2 Shrooms, 1 Pine and 1 Rose.
  • If your villager is killed, get 1 herb.
  • If it's a werewolf, 1 shroom.
  • If it's a miscellaneous, 1 Pine.
  • If it's a solo killer, 1 Rose. Due to your scent, you cannot be killed by the first attack of the same player BUT your role (w desc in this case) will be revealed to that player. Aura: Unknown
Team: Miscellaneous
6:29 PM
You cannot use more ingredients than needed for 1 potion and can only use OR brew 1 potion per night. Herb + Shroom: Pot. Of Sincerity
  • At night, select one of your cards and an enemy card. You both will be told what that card selected is.
-# (including it's description.) Herb + Pine: Pot. Of Resentment
  • At night select an enemy card. If one of your cards dies, kill that card. If no one dies, roleblock it for a day and a night. Herb + Rose: Pot. Of Recovery
  • Make a Villager decoy for a card. If that card is attacked, the decoy dies instead. Everyone is told if it's a decoy and will give you 1 herb if killed. Decoy stays until Herbalist dies.
Everyone is told if the decoy dies and this description is revealed to everyone but not the ability's name. Shroom + Pine: Pot. Of Evaluation
  • At night, Pick an enemy card to protect. If that card is saved from an attack, all of your cards will get a day protection. Everyone is told if one of your cards are protected by Evaluation. Protection stays for both you and the selected player till the intended attack occurs. Shroom + Rose: Pot. Of Virulence
  • Poison any amount of your cards. You will be told who has a copy of your cards poisoned and will be poisoned as well. Cards poisoned cannot vote, do a werewolf kill or attack as solo for a day. Pine + Rose: Pot. Of Revisitation
  • Revive a villager/miscellaneous card of an enemy as your own (R9, etc.). That card is protected for a phase. The inventory stays the same as it was the moment of death.

Engineer (12)

Starts with 200 metal and gains 30 metal every night. At night can build one of these structures:
  • Sentry costs 130 metal. Sentry is placed on one of your cards; cards attacking it will be killed by Sentry and their protection will be bypassed (but it won't protect the card from attacks). After 2 attacks it dies. Engineer can use 150 metal ONCE to repair it and activate it same night (but it won't change the target on which it is placed)
  • Dispenser costs 100 metal. Dispenser is placed between 2 neighbour cards, heals both of them so they won't die at night, dies after protecting from 2 attacks and cannot be repaired.
  • Teleporter costs 100 metal. Engineer can place an entrance and an exit on one of his attackers and on an opponent's card. Attacking that card afterwards will ignore protection, Teleporter doesn't count as a protection.
  • Everything, after placed, will turn on the next night.
  • Moving one of the structures at night costs 50 metal and Engineer cannot build new structures while moving one of them.
Alignment: Villager Aura: Unknown

Engineer (12)

Starts with 200 metal and gains 30 metal every night. At night can build one of these structures:
  • Sentry costs 130 metal. Sentry is placed on one of your cards; cards attacking it will be killed by Sentry and their protection will be bypassed (but it won't protect the card from attacks). After 2 attacks it dies. Engineer can use 150 metal ONCE to repair it and activate it same night (but it won't change the target on which it is placed)
  • Dispenser costs 100 metal. Dispenser is placed between 2 neighbour cards, heals both of them so they won't die at night, dies after protecting from 2 attacks and cannot be repaired.
  • Teleporter costs 100 metal. Engineer can place an entrance and an exit on one of his attackers and on an opponent's card. Attacking that card afterwards will ignore protection, Teleporter doesn't count as a protection.
  • Everything, after placed, will turn on the next night.
  • Moving one of the structures at night costs 50 metal and Engineer cannot build new structures while moving one of them.
Alignment: Villager Aura: Unknown
